                        one part, and (2) William Robinson, William Farrer and William Babbington of
                        the Inner Temple, London, esqs., of the other part, bargain and sale by (1)
                        to (2) of the twelfth part of the manors of Bawreper, Cranes, Bradley,
                        Stevington, Northfarram, Bullesdens, Bentworthe, Roch Court and Froyle,
                        Hampshire, and the twelfth part of the advowsons of the churches of
                        Steventon and Bradley, Hampshire. Endorsed with eleven powers of attorney
                        made by (1), and a memorandum rel to delivery of seisin of the properties to
